revision.text:
{{unreferenced|date=March 2010}} {{Infobox video game | title = Brothers in Arms: Art of War | image = Brothersinarms mobile box.jpg | developer = [[Gameloft]] | publisher = [[Gameloft]] | series = ''[[Brothers in Arms (video game series)|Brothers in Arms]]'' | platforms = [[Java Platform, Micro Edition]] | released = {{vgrelease|NA|March 11, 2008}} | genre = [[Shoot 'em up|Top-down shooter]] | modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] }}
[[Image:Brothersinarms mobile1.jpg|left|thumb|150px|Typical gameplay screenshot.]] '''''Brothers in Arms: Art of War''''' is a game developed and published by [[Gameloft]] for [[mobile games|mobile phones]], based on Gearbox's [[Brothers in Arms (series)|''Brothers in Arms'' series]].
''Art of War'' is chiefly a [[Shoot 'em up|top-down shooter]], featuring 13 missions in 3 campaigns, including [[Operation Market Garden]]. The game also includes parachute missions, [[Shoot 'em up#Tube and rail shooters|rail shooter]] plane, tank and boat missions, as well as a destructible environment.
