{{Infobox album | name = Cake & Ice Cream 2 | type = album | artist = [[Messy Marv]] | cover = Cake & Ice Cream 2.jpg | alt = | released = March 10, 2009 | recorded = | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Rap]] | length = 1:18:01 | label = Siccness.net<ref>http://www.allmusic.com/album/cake-and-ice-cream-vol-2-mw0000808954/releases</ref> | producer = Messy Marv<ref>http://www.allmusic.com/album/cake-and-ice-cream-vol-2-mw0000808954/credits</ref> | prev_title = [[Cake & Ice Cream]] | prev_year = 2008 | next_title = [[Blow (Messy Marv & Berner album)|Blow]] | next_year = 2009 }}
'''''Cake & Ice Cream 2''''' is the 15th studio album by American rapper [[Messy Marv]]. The 2nd album of his ''Cake & Ice Cream'' trilogy, it peaked at #39 on the [[R&B/Hip-Hop Albums]] chart, #25 on the Heatseekers Albums chart, and at #12 on the [[Rap Albums]] chart.<ref>{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=messy marv|chart=all}}</ref> It is one of the most successful albums of his career. ''Cake & Ice Cream 2'' includes guest appearances from [[E-40]] and [[The Jacka]], among others, and also performances by [[Gucci Mane]], [[Mistah F.A.B.]], [[Yukmouth]] & [[Turf Talk]]. As of April 2009, it had sold 5,222 copies in the U.S.<ref>http://haziqali.wordpress.com/2009/04/29/soundscan-for-this-past-week/</ref>
"Talk Baseball" and "Killa" are both diss tracks at cousin/rapper [[San Quinn]], while Quinn himself appears on ''Cake & Ice Cream 2'' and disses Messy Marv in a song called "Fence Hopper".
According to [[Allmusic]], "The [[Fillmore District]]’s own Messy Marv never rests, as he gives hungry fans another taste of his unique West Coast flavor on the mixtape release ''Cake & Ice Cream 2''. The album documents the beef between Marv and fellow Bay Area representative San Quinn with each rapper throwing shots on solo diss tracks (San Quinn labels Marv a “Fence Hopper” and Marv gets personal on “Killa”). A handful of respected northern Cali artists also put in guest appearances."
==Track listing== <ref>http://www.allmusic.com/album/cake-ice-cream-mixtape-volume-2-mw0000808954</ref> {| class="wikitable" |- ! # ! Title ! length |- | 1 | Cake and Ice Cream, V. II | 3:36 |- | 2 | Talk Baseball <small>([[San Quinn]] Diss!!)</small> | 2:45 |- | 3 | Fence Hopper <small>(Messy Marv Diss!!) [performed by San Quinn]</small> | 3:30 |- | 4 | Killa <small>(San Quinn Diss!!)</small> | 4:11 |- | 5 | Enemy | 3:25 |- | 6 | Like Me | 3:49 |- | 7 | Down for My Block <small>(performed by [[Mistah F.A.B.]] & [[Turf Talk]] featuring [[E-40]])</small> | 4:22 |- | 8 | Money Bags Shawty <small>(performed by [[Gucci Mane]])</small> | 4:31 |- | 9 | U Heezy | 3:53 |- | 10 | U Wit Me | 3:11 |- | 11 | Let Me Pimp or Let Me Die <small>(performed by [[Suga Free]])</small> | 3:27 |- | 12 | No Love <small>(performed by Matt Blaque)</small> | 3:28 |- | 13 | Menage | 3:45 |- | 14 | Fu#$n Wit It <small>(performed by [[Yukmouth]] featuring [[Smigg Dirtee]], Gonzoe, I-Rocc & [[The Jacka]])</small> | 4:42 |- | 15 | Trap | 4:04 |- | 16 | Angel | 4:35 |- | 17 | Underneath | 3:50 |- | 18 | Candy | 4:51 |- | 19 | Imma Hustla <small>(featuring The Jacka)</small> | 4:42 |- | 20 | Girl <small>(performed by Jessica Rabbit)</small> | 3:24 |}
