'''GiftRapped''' is a digital company that creates fully customized [[hip-hop]] songs and [[music video]]s.<ref>{{cite news|title=That's a Rap  Giving Hip-Hop for the Holidays|url=http://www.urbandaddy.com/ntl/entertainment/12012/Gift_Rapped_Giving_Hip_Hop_for_the_Holidays_National_NTL_Website|accessdate=29 March 2013|publisher=[[UrbanDaddy]]|date=December 8, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=McGauley|first=Joe|title=Custom hip-hop ditties for you and your peeps|url=http://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/gift-rapped_music_services|work=Thrillist.com|publisher=[[Thrillist]]|accessdate=29 March 2013}}</ref>  Founded in 2010 by hip-hop artists Jay Kila and Thunda Dan, it has been featured on [[Today (U.S. TV program)|The Today Show]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Whatsup, ladies? Kathie Lee and Hoda get a 'gift rap'|url=http://allday.today.com/_news/2011/12/07/9274105-whatsup-ladies-kathie-lee-and-hoda-get-a-gift-rap?lite|work=TheTodayShow.com|publisher=The Today Show|accessdate=29 March 2013}}</ref>  Most songs created by GiftRapped are about individuals and used for special occasions.  GiftRapped is based in [[New York City]] and operates mostly through the internet.{{citation needed|date=April 2013}}

